Unfortunately, this solution uses the Hadamard and Pauli-X gates, which are not allowed. We are asked to use only the RX, RY, and CNOT gates, and to use gradient descent or another optimization method to estimate the parameters. Let us try to build the simplest circuit that could plausibly produce the Bell state. We must have at least one 2-qubit gate because the Bell state is entangled. On the other hand, the Bell state cannot be generated by CNOT gates alone, because CNOTs permute the computational basis but the Bell state is not in the computational basis. Our candidate circuit will apply an RX gate to each qubit, followed by a CNOT gate.
